<header><title>Got Nouns?</title><date>2006-06-22</date></header>
<entry>
    <p>Sometimes you can glean a lot of folk philosophy from language. Here are the <a href="http://www.cnn.com/2006/WORLD/europe/06/21/popular.nouns.ap/index.html">25 most common nouns</a> in English, which I think reveal quite a bit about the Anglosphere sense of life:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>time</li>
      <li>person</li>
      <li>year</li>
      <li>way</li>
      <li>day</li>
      <li>thing</li>
      <li>man</li>
      <li>world</li>
      <li>life</li>
      <li>hand</li>
      <li>part</li>
      <li>child</li>
      <li>eye</li>
      <li>woman</li>
      <li>place</li>
      <li>work</li>
      <li>week</li>
      <li>case</li>
      <li>point</li>
      <li>government</li>
      <li>company</li>
      <li>number</li>
      <li>group</li>
      <li>problem</li>
      <li>fact</li>
    </ol>
    <p>I'd like to see this list compared to lists from other languages...</p>
